01:17:32,523 --> 01:17:35,275
MAN [LISPING]: Look at Cohan.
He's got them lined up at the box office.

1401
01:17:35,484 --> 01:17:38,486
I've never seen the guy.
Got his name all over the place. Look at that.

1402
01:17:38,696 --> 01:17:41,364
"Cohan and Harris present
George Washington, Jr.

1403
01:17:41,574 --> 01:17:44,743
Starring the author and composer,
George M. Cohan."

1404
01:17:44,952 --> 01:17:47,329
I wonder what the M is for.
Oh, modesty.

1405
01:17:47,538 --> 01:17:49,039
- Hello, Mr. Foy.
- How are you?

1406
01:17:49,248 --> 01:17:50,790
- Enjoyed your show last night.
- Thank you.

1407
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:53,084
You always appear
in the kind of stuff I like.

1408
01:17:53,294 --> 01:17:54,961
Thank you. That's very nice of you.

1409
01:17:55,171 --> 01:17:57,172
"George M. Cohan and his royal family.

1410
01:17:57,381 --> 01:18:00,759
Books and lyrics, music, and direction
by George M. Cohan.

1411
01:18:00,968 --> 01:18:02,594
Printed by Sam Divensky."

1412
01:18:02,803 --> 01:18:04,721
That must be Cohan's alias.

1413
01:18:04,930 --> 01:18:07,432
Certainly keeps himself in billing,
this George M. Cohan.

1414
01:18:07,642 --> 01:18:09,893
Don't memorize that one.
There's plenty all over town.

1415
01:18:10,102 --> 01:18:14,606
I'd like to forget it. Say, listen,
you connected with this turkey?

1416
01:18:14,815 --> 01:18:16,650
Turkey? I hear it's pretty good.

1417
01:18:16,859 --> 01:18:18,735
It's a malicious rumor to gyp the public.

1418
01:18:18,944 --> 01:18:21,446
Who is this guy Cohan? Where is he from?
What is he, an upstart?

1419
01:18:21,656 --> 01:18:25,283
Oh, he's been through the mill.
Small-time and big-time vaudeville, rep shows.

1420
01:18:25,493 --> 01:18:28,203
- Even followed dog acts.
- Must have looked like an encore.

1421
01:18:28,412 --> 01:18:31,706
- Say, uh, is he as good as Foy?
- Who?

1422
01:18:31,916 --> 01:18:33,583
Foy, Foy, Eddie Foy.

1423
01:18:33,793 --> 01:18:35,377
Oh, pardon me.

1424
01:18:35,586 --> 01:18:38,546
Pardon me, I didn't quite catch the name.
Would you mind spraying it again?

1425
01:18:38,756 --> 01:18:40,465
Eddie Foy.

1426
01:18:40,675 --> 01:18:43,385
The star that's got the big show
down the street with a chorus of 70.

1427
01:18:43,594 --> 01:18:46,221
[LISPING] Why, I thought they looked
a little younger than that.

1428
01:18:46,430 --> 01:18:48,932
I hear now that Cohan's in town,
Foy's gonna retire.

1429
01:18:49,141 --> 01:18:50,725
Foy won't retire till he's 90.

1430
01:18:50,935 --> 01:18:53,311
Is it gonna take him that long
to discover he has no talent?

1431
01:18:53,521 --> 01:18:56,147
They tell me when he tries to sing,
the orchestra puts up umbrellas.

1432
01:18:56,357 --> 01:19:00,276
Tries to sing? Why, he's a genius.
He keeps his audience glued to the seats.

1433
01:19:00,486 --> 01:19:03,738
That's one way of keeping them in the theater.
Cohan does it with talent. Look.

1434
01:19:03,948 --> 01:19:07,283
Produces his own plays, writes his own books,
lyrics and music, plays the leads...

1435
01:19:07,493 --> 01:19:10,078
- ...and is a great dancer.
- He dances, eh?

1436
01:19:10,287 --> 01:19:11,621
When does he get time to practice?

1437
01:19:11,831 --> 01:19:14,833
When you write your own plays,
you don't have to. Cohan's done all right.

1438
01:19:15,042 --> 01:19:18,628
He's given the world "Yankee Doodle Dandy."
What's Foy done for his country?

1439
01:19:19,380 --> 01:19:20,839
He gave them seven kids.

1440
01:19:21,048 --> 01:19:22,507
- Does he dance?
- One of the best.

1441
01:19:22,717 --> 01:19:24,801
When does he get time to practice?

1442
01:19:25,386 --> 01:19:28,138
Say, listen, young fella,
my name's Eddie Foy.

1443
01:19:28,347 --> 01:19:30,515
I know it. I'm George M. Cohan.

1444
01:19:30,725 --> 01:19:33,226
Oh, so you're Cohan?

1445
01:19:33,436 --> 01:19:35,562
Well, if I said anything accidental
to make you mad...

1446
01:19:35,771 --> 01:19:37,313
...I want you to know
I'm darn glad I did.

1447
01:19:37,523 --> 01:19:40,900
I don't blame you. I'd feel the same way
if I were up against Cohan.

1448
01:19:41,110 --> 01:19:43,069
- What do like to drink?
- Oh, moxie.

1449
01:19:43,279 --> 01:19:46,239
I can supply it. The attraction inside
is a whole lot bigger than I am.

1450
01:19:46,449 --> 01:19:48,450
Come and see when your show closes.

1451
